001package edu.cnm.deepdive.teamle;
002
003import android.os.Bundle;
004import androidx.annotation.NonNull;
005import androidx.navigation.NavDirections;
006import java.lang.IllegalArgumentException;
007import java.lang.Object;
008import java.lang.Override;
009import java.lang.String;
010import java.lang.SuppressWarnings;
011import java.util.HashMap;
012
013public class NavigationGraphDirections {
014  private NavigationGraphDirections() {
015  }
016
017  @NonNull
018  public static ExplainPermissions explainPermissions(@NonNull String[] permissionsToExplain,
019      @NonNull String[] permissionsToRequest) {
020    return new ExplainPermissions(permissionsToExplain, permissionsToRequest);
021  }
022
023  public static class ExplainPermissions implements NavDirections {
024    private final HashMap arguments = new HashMap();
025
026    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
027    private ExplainPermissions(@NonNull String[] permissionsToExplain,
028        @NonNull String[] permissionsToRequest) {
029      if (permissionsToExplain == null) {
030        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Argument \"permissions_to_explain\" is marked as non-null but was passed a null value.");
031      }
032      this.arguments.put("permissions_to_explain", permissionsToExplain);
033      if (permissionsToRequest == null) {
034        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Argument \"permissions_to_request\" is marked as non-null but was passed a null value.");
035      }
036      this.arguments.put("permissions_to_request", permissionsToRequest);
037    }
038
039    @NonNull
040    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
041    public ExplainPermissions setPermissionsToExplain(@NonNull String[] permissionsToExplain) {
042      if (permissionsToExplain == null) {
043        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Argument \"permissions_to_explain\" is marked as non-null but was passed a null value.");
044      }
045      this.arguments.put("permissions_to_explain", permissionsToExplain);
046      return this;
047    }
048
049    @NonNull
050    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
051    public ExplainPermissions setPermissionsToRequest(@NonNull String[] permissionsToRequest) {
052      if (permissionsToRequest == null) {
053        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Argument \"permissions_to_request\" is marked as non-null but was passed a null value.");
054      }
055      this.arguments.put("permissions_to_request", permissionsToRequest);
056      return this;
057    }
058
059    @Override
060    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
061    @NonNull
062    public Bundle getArguments() {
063      Bundle __result = new Bundle();
064      if (arguments.containsKey("permissions_to_explain")) {
065        String[] permissionsToExplain = (String[]) arguments.get("permissions_to_explain");
066        __result.putStringArray("permissions_to_explain", permissionsToExplain);
067      }
068      if (arguments.containsKey("permissions_to_request")) {
069        String[] permissionsToRequest = (String[]) arguments.get("permissions_to_request");
070        __result.putStringArray("permissions_to_request", permissionsToRequest);
071      }
072      return __result;
073    }
074
075    @Override
076    public int getActionId() {
077      return R.id.explain_permissions;
078    }
079
080    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
081    @NonNull
082    public String[] getPermissionsToExplain() {
083      return (String[]) arguments.get("permissions_to_explain");
084    }
085
086    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
087    @NonNull
088    public String[] getPermissionsToRequest() {
089      return (String[]) arguments.get("permissions_to_request");
090    }
091
092    @Override
093    public boolean equals(Object object) {
094      if (this == object) {
095          return true;
096      }
097      if (object == null || getClass() != object.getClass()) {
098          return false;
099      }
100      ExplainPermissions that = (ExplainPermissions) object;
101      if (arguments.containsKey("permissions_to_explain") != that.arguments.containsKey("permissions_to_explain")) {
102        return false;
103      }
104      if (getPermissionsToExplain() != null ? !getPermissionsToExplain().equals(that.getPermissionsToExplain()) : that.getPermissionsToExplain() != null) {
105        return false;
106      }
107      if (arguments.containsKey("permissions_to_request") != that.arguments.containsKey("permissions_to_request")) {
108        return false;
109      }
110      if (getPermissionsToRequest() != null ? !getPermissionsToRequest().equals(that.getPermissionsToRequest()) : that.getPermissionsToRequest() != null) {
111        return false;
112      }
113      if (getActionId() != that.getActionId()) {
114        return false;
115      }
116      return true;
117    }
118
119    @Override
120    public int hashCode() {
121      int result = 1;
122      result = 31 * result + java.util.Arrays.hashCode(getPermissionsToExplain());
123      result = 31 * result + java.util.Arrays.hashCode(getPermissionsToRequest());
124      result = 31 * result + getActionId();
125      return result;
126    }
127
128    @Override
129    public String toString() {
130      return "ExplainPermissions(actionId=" + getActionId() + "){"
131          + "permissionsToExplain=" + getPermissionsToExplain()
132          + ", permissionsToRequest=" + getPermissionsToRequest()
133          + "}";
134    }
135  }
136}
